      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Commanders",
        "body": "The dust settles on another NFL Draft in D.C., and the Commanders - fresh off a <strong>5-12 thud that left them third in the NFC East</strong> - emerged with six picks that scream rebuild, not reload. General manager Adam Peters gambled big at No. 7 overall, snagging Ohio State linebacker Sonny Styles, a \"wicked smart\" heatseeker analysts peg as a Week 1 starter anchoring Dan Quinn's defense - think Fred Warner 2.0, plugging the gaps left by last year's league-worst unit that sank Jayden Daniels' arm talent. Round 5 brought Tennessee edge Joshua Josephs for pass-rush juice and Clemson wideout Antonio Williams to juice the offense, passing on flashier corners while bulking the depth chart with Chig Okonkwo at tight end and Kaytron Allen in the backfield. Nine undrafted free agents later, Peters' roster hits 81, blending youth into a scheme that fits Quinn's schemes like a glove. Bleacher Report slapped them with the \"Rebuilding\" tag - harsh, but fair after injuries torpedoed Super Bowl dreams. Styles could flip that script fast. <strong>Watch rookie minicamp next week</strong>: if these kids mesh, Daniels gets his shield, and Washington claws back into the East hunt come September.",
        "updated": "Updated April 29, 2026"
